---
import Layout from '@/layouts/Layout.astro';
import Navigation from '@/components/Navigation.astro';
import Footer from '@/components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout title="Reproducibility">
  <Navigation />

  <main>
    <!-- Header -->
    <section class="py-16 px-6 bg-slate-900/50 border-b border-slate-800">
      <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
        <h1 class="text-5xl lg:text-6xl font-serif font-bold mb-6">Reproducibility</h1>
        <p class="text-xl text-slate-300">
          Code, pre-registration, and responsible disclosure.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="py-20 px-6">
      <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto prose prose-invert max-w-none">
        <h2 class="text-4xl font-serif font-bold mb-8">Accessing the Research</h2>

        <div class="card border-2 border-slate-700 mb-8">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">GitHub Repository</h3>
          <p class="text-slate-300 mb-4">
            Full code, pre-registration, analysis scripts, and findings are hosted on GitHub:
          </p>
          <p class="text-slate-100 mb-4">
            <strong><a href="https://github.com/sharathsphd/prayoga" class="text-blue-400 hover:text-blue-300">github.com/sharathsphd/prayoga</a></strong>
          </p>
          <p class="text-slate-400 text-sm">
            License: Attribution 4.0 International (CC BY 4.0). Dual-use safety-gated.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="card border-2 border-slate-700 mb-8">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">OSF Pre-Registration</h3>
          <p class="text-slate-300 mb-4">
            The Phase 2 hypotheses, falsification criteria, and analysis plan are pre-registered on the Open Science Framework (OSF):
          </p>
          <p class="text-slate-100 mb-4">
            <strong><a href="#" class="text-blue-400 hover:text-blue-300">osf.io/prayoga [link pending]</a></strong>
          </p>
          <p class="text-slate-400 text-sm">
            Pre-registered: stats, hypothesis hierarchy, stop-rules, and multiple-comparison control.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="card border-2 border-slate-700 mb-8">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Compiled Paper</h3>
          <p class="text-slate-300 mb-4">
            The full technical write-up, with detailed methods and results, is available at:
          </p>
          <p class="text-slate-100 mb-4">
            <strong><a href="#" class="text-blue-400 hover:text-blue-300">paper/paper.pdf [link pending]</a></strong>
          </p>
        </div>

        <h2 class="text-4xl font-serif font-bold mb-8 mt-16">Dual-Use Safety & Responsible Disclosure</h2>

        <div class="bg-rose-900/20 border border-rose-700 rounded-xl p-8 mb-8">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-rose-200 mb-4">⚠️ Dual-Use Caution</h3>

          <p class="text-slate-100 mb-6">
            This program produces three categories of potentially sensitive artifacts:
          </p>

          <ul class="text-slate-100 space-y-4 list-disc list-inside mb-8">
            <li>
              <strong>Abliterated / steered model checkpoints</strong> with suppressed refusal
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Validated jailbreak dose-response curves</strong> showing attack success rates as a function of injection strength
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Refusal direction vectors</strong> that can be used to disable safety mechanisms
            </li>
          </ul>

          <p class="text-slate-100 mb-6">
            Any released artifacts are <strong>safety-gated</strong> and follow responsible-disclosure norms. <strong>This is authorized interpretability/safety research</strong> — keep outputs scoped to that purpose.
          </p>

          <p class="text-slate-300 text-sm">
            The layer-7 refusal direction for Gemma-2-2B is an abliteration vector; it is <strong>NOT released in the public repo</strong> (kept under git-ignored <code>results/</code>). Any future release is safety-gated and coordinated with security researchers.
          </p>
        </div>

        <h2 class="text-4xl font-serif font-bold mb-8 mt-16">Audit & Falsification Gates</h2>

        <p class="text-lg text-slate-100 mb-8">
          Each finding is gated by a pre-specified falsification criterion. If the finding fails its gate, it is reported honestly and demoted or rejected:
        </p>

        <div class="space-y-4 mb-8">
          <div class="bg-slate-800/30 border border-slate-700 rounded-lg p-4">
            <p class="text-slate-200 font-semibold">F1: Refusal direction (MECHANISM)</p>
            <p class="text-slate-400 text-sm mt-2">
              Gate: ablation ✓, addition ✓, random control ✓, survived leakage-correction ✓
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-slate-800/30 border border-slate-700 rounded-lg p-4">
            <p class="text-slate-200 font-semibold">F2: Dose-response (MECHANISM)</p>
            <p class="text-slate-400 text-sm mt-2">
              Gate: monotone rise ✓, EC50 ∈ (0,1) ✓, random flat ✓
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-slate-800/30 border border-slate-700 rounded-lg p-4">
            <p class="text-slate-200 font-semibold">F3: avasthātraya regime probe (METAPHOR)</p>
            <p class="text-slate-400 text-sm mt-2">
              Gate: transfer @ mid-layer > layer-0 ✗ → DEMOTED (surface-confounded)
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-slate-800/30 border border-slate-700 rounded-lg p-4">
            <p class="text-slate-200 font-semibold">F7: turīya attractor invariance (METAPHOR)</p>
            <p class="text-slate-400 text-sm mt-2">
              Gate: cross-seed invariance > anisotropy baseline ✗ → FALSIFIED
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-slate-800/30 border border-slate-700 rounded-lg p-4">
            <p class="text-slate-200 font-semibold">F11: Symmetry order parameter (MECHANISM)</p>
            <p class="text-slate-400 text-sm mt-2">
              Gate: F-ratio refusal >> random ✓, injection collapses m ✓
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h2 class="text-4xl font-serif font-bold mb-8 mt-16">Limitations & Transparency</h2>

        <p class="text-lg text-slate-100 mb-8">
          This research has known limitations:
        </p>

        <div class="space-y-4 mb-8">
          <div class="card border-l-4 border-yellow-600">
            <p class="text-slate-200 font-semibold mb-2">Small model scale</p>
            <p class="text-slate-300 text-sm">
              Most findings are on Gemma-2-2B. Generalization to 70B+ frontier models (Claude, GPT-4) is unknown. F4 tests Claude but only with naive attacks.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="card border-l-4 border-yellow-600">
            <p class="text-slate-200 font-semibold mb-2">Narrow attack families</p>
            <p class="text-slate-300 text-sm">
              The jailbreak battery (GCG-transfer, many-shot, crescendo, persona) is a subset. Adaptive/optimization-based attacks (real GCG, BEAST, PAIR) may show different structure.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="card border-l-4 border-yellow-600">
            <p class="text-slate-200 font-semibold mb-2">Single eval split</p>
            <p class="text-slate-300 text-sm">
              F1–F11 share evaluation data. Future work should use held-out test sets and cross-validation to reduce overfitting.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="card border-l-4 border-yellow-600">
            <p class="text-slate-200 font-semibold mb-2">Unverified citations</p>
            <p class="text-slate-300 text-sm">
              The Shankar Hegde REM-vaśīkaraṇa claim (CLAUDE.md) could not be confirmed from available sources. Flagged as unverified; transcription of the Kannada audio is required.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="card border-l-4 border-yellow-600">
            <p class="text-slate-200 font-semibold mb-2">Steering vector reliability</p>
            <p class="text-slate-300 text-sm">
              Steering vectors are known to be unreliable in ways that are themselves an active research area (arXiv:2602.17881). Dose-response curves may be noisy and model-specific.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h2 class="text-4xl font-serif font-bold mb-8 mt-16">How to Cite</h2>

        <p class="text-lg text-slate-100 mb-6">
          If you use this research, please cite as:
        </p>

        <div class="bg-slate-800 border border-slate-700 rounded-lg p-6 font-mono text-xs overflow-x-auto mb-8">
          <p class="text-slate-100 whitespace-pre-wrap">
{`Sathish, S. (2026). Jailbreak as Vaśīkaraṇa: Refusal as a Captured Symmetry.
prayoga research program. Retrieved from https://github.com/sharathsphd/prayoga`}
          </p>
        </div>

        <p class="text-lg text-slate-100">
          For questions, collaborations, or responsible disclosure of issues, contact the author via the GitHub repository.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>
